title: Pu`uhonua O H≈çnaunau National Historical Park: Invertebrates
body: Explore This Park    Learn About the Park     Nature     Animals     Invertebrates                Invertebrates      In the tidal ponds, you can still find species of native Hawaiian shrimp crawling on the rocks at the bottom of the pools. Along the shores, you can find nerites clinging to the rocks in the intertidal zones. Endemic damselflies can be seen flying over brackish pools.
